<div id="main">
  <div class="bar"></div>

  <div class="container">
    <h2>Everything a chess player needs</h2>
    <p>If you play chess, and love chess, I assume you've tried many things to get better at chess. Tactics trainers, chess lectures, driving hours to private lessons or trying to hack something together online, etc. Well my freind, look no further, I got what you need.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="features container">
    <div id="timeline">
      <span id="step-1" class="step">1</span>
      <span id="step-2" class="step">2</span>
      <span id="step-3" class="step">3</span>
    </div>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>Ability to connect</h3>
      <p>On jackschess.com you can connect with anyone in the world right next to a chessboard. Whether it is Uncle Tom or GM Magnus Carlsen, if they accept an invite to your jackschess room, you guys will be connected with a board on the same screen. All in your browser, over the internet.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>The best tools</h3>
      <p>A jackschess room is what every player dreams of. Enjoy the best player in the world giving you analysis when you need it, PGN annotation with notes, PGN uploader, drawing tools, ability to set up and save positions, all in one screen. Yeah I know, thank me later.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="feature">
      <h3>Teachers/learners community</h3>
      <p>The number one best way to learn chess is with others that are better or that want to learn too. Let's make jackschess the community of teachers and learners. This internet thing is pretty cool, we should use it to help us get better at chess.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="screenshot">
      <img alt="Team-overview" src="/assets/images/marketing/me_and_im.png">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bar"></div>

  <div id="overview" class="container">
    <section>
      <h2>A dream for chess coaches</h2>
      <p>Teaching the game of chess is hard, but it's never the hardest part of being a chess coach, which is super annoying. We've all been there with Skype and ICC/chess.com fighting eachother for screen space. Group lessons are a mess. You keep awkwardly looking down to set up puzzles from the book in your lap. The list goes on. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NEN5baraAaQ" target="_blank">Cars are about to start driving themselves</a>, you'd think someone can make something to help chess coaches right? Yeah, I thought the same too. That's why I built jackschess and designed {{#link-to 'home.signup'}}accounts{{/link-to}} just for coaches. You have your own "chess room" at your own URL with a personalized toolbox of positions, games, puzzles, etc.</p>
    </section>
